init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is now a third world country.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Soeurette Morley has been elected president for life and has been ruling the country with an iron fist for the past 50 years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Soeurette Morley decides to take the U.S. back to the top by any means necessary.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She decides to invade the other countries that did not go into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She decides to do this because she feels that the U.S. has been wronged and that the U.S. is entitled to take what

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Soeurette Morley is a very strong and determined woman.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is now in a very bad position.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is now hated by everyone in the United States.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is forced to go into hiding.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is forced to go into exile.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And she is forced to live the rest of her life in shame.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is now a democracy again.
